Scenario: A search input updates a large filtered list. Typing becomes laggy because rendering the list blocks the main thread.

Code:

function SearchPage() {
  const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
  const filtered = expensiveFilter(query);

  return (
    <>
      <input value={query} onChange={(e) => setQuery(e.target.value)} />
      <BigList items={filtered} />
    </>
  );
}

Explain how concurrent rendering features can improve responsiveness here, and identify the React API most appropriate for this scenario.

Scenario: An engineer observes that a component renders twice during development in Strict Mode and assumes concurrent rendering is causing duplicate commits.

Code:

function Dashboard() {
  useEffect(() => {
    console.log('Effect mounted');
  }, []);

  console.log('Render');

  return <Widget />;
}

Explain why this behavior happens and clarify the relationship between Strict Mode and concurrent rendering.

Scenario: A team mutates shared state during render.

Code:

let cache = [];

function ProductList({ products }) {
  cache.push(products.length);

  return products.map((p) => <Item key={p.id} product={p} />);
}

Why is this implementation dangerous under concurrent rendering, and what architectural principle is being violated?
